BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13
14
SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14
15
in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 865.71 of Title 19, unless there
15
16
is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16
17
A. As used in this section, “data center” means any facility
17
18
that primarily contains electronic equipment used to process, store,
18
19
and transmit digital information and uses environmental control
19
20
equipment to maintain the proper conditions for the operation of
20
21
electronic equipment.
21
22
B. On and after the effective date of this act, any individual
22
23
or company intending to construct a data center in unincorporated
23
24
county land of this state shall:
24
Req. No. 2836 Page 1

1
1. Notify the board of county commissioners of the county where
1
2
such data center is intended to be located by the submission of a
2
3
notice of intent, which shall be read aloud and entered into the
3
4
minutes of the next meeting of the board. Such notice shall clearly
4
5
state the name of the individual or company intending to construct a
5
6
data center, the proposed location within the county, and plans
6
7
relating to such data center. A copy of such notice shall be
7
8
published by such individual or company in a newspaper of general
8
9
circulation within the county weekly for at least three (3)
9
10
consecutive weeks following the reading of such notice; and
10
11
2. In coordination with the board of county commissioners,
11
12
schedule at least three public meetings, with at least two (2) weeks
12
13
between each meeting, to take place at a convenient location within
13
14
the county near the location where the individual or company intends
14
15
to construct a data center. Notice of such meetings shall be
15
16
published by such individual or company in a newspaper of general
16
17
circulation within the county daily for at least two (2) days
17
18
preceding such meeting. At such meetings, such individual or
18
19
company shall present the plans relating to such data center and
19
20
answer any questions from the board of county commissioners or
20
21
members of the public who attend such meeting.
21
22
C. The board of county commissioners, after certifying that the
22
23
provisions of subsection B of this section have been followed, shall
23
24
schedule a meeting to approve or disapprove the construction of a
24
Req. No. 2836 Page 2

1
data center. Notice for such meeting shall be given by publication
1
2
in a newspaper of general circulation within the county for at least
2
3
three (3) consecutive weeks preceding the meeting. Such meeting
3
4
shall allow for the individual or company intending to construct the
4
5
data center to present the plans relating to such data center and
5
6
any additional information requested by the board of county
6
7
commissioners, as well as allow for public comment from members of
7
8
the public who attend such meeting. Such presentation and public
8
9
comment shall happen prior to the vote to approve or disapprove the
9
10
construction of a data center. No vote shall take place until all
10
11
members of the public who wish to comment have had the chance to
11
12
express such comment.
12
13
SECTION 2. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
13
14
of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
14
15
declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
15
16
be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
